race.comment: Competitive. CRESTA RUN (3) led and won easily before pulling up with an issue when well-supported at Randwick. Bounced straight back, winning a CL2 by a space at Coonabarabran, backed off the map. Has the early speed to manage the awkward barrier and will be tough to peg back. CRIMSON BONNET (9) has also won two of her last three, and the form stacks right up as well. Should enjoy a soft run and threaten. FLYING ARGYLE (4) has been around the mark without winning. He's up to this if he could find his best form and the top hoop rides for the first time, replacing the apprentice. Draws low and keep him onside. I AM A WINNER (1) came from well back on the bend to score last time out over 950m at Moree. Should be winding up late again.
